nd the trick photography of Germanic horror films. I even gave a talk on myCambridge days at a rather pathetic English Ladies Club, to which shebelonged. And to top the treat, I told her the plot of my next novel (CameraLucida).

One afternoon, in March or early April, 1930, she peeped into my roomand, being admitted, handed me the duplicate of a typewritten sheet,numbered 444. It was, she <61> said, a tentative episode in her interminabletale, which would soon display more deletions than insert